urrently among the least vulnerable, could be considered at future risk on account of their rapidly growing oil consumption relative to domestic supply. Similarly, Thailand and India could be at greater risk in the future given their persistently high dependence on imported oil.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "6cfbdc26-209f-457a-b7ec-09ba4ab101d3": {"__data__": {"id_": "6cfbdc26-209f-457a-b7ec-09ba4ab101d3", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/overcoming-vulnerability-rising-oil-prices", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Overcoming Vulnerability to Rising Oil Prices", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/overcoming-vulnerability-rising-oil-prices", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "44880a15c4af4b5a6845f356ee2a63a648d3f11016d6538a0b070c07e4442260"}, "2": {"node_id": "ff69eb25-7036-44f2-939f-6820b0100242", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/overcoming-vulnerability-rising-oil-prices", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "ce8ad0343a65485c7d149980655f747dcf73234b632b79753daf036c9ceead3d"}}, "hash": "3429ecb9e1916c125be995f83cc8237e345ca92535595c37c26bb1ff327726f8", "text": "It should also be Chapter 3: National vulnerability to oil price rises 49 Table 3-1 Ranking of countries based on weighted dimension scores and composite OPVI Rank Countries OPVI Strength Performance Low-oi