tps://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/overcoming-vulnerability-rising-oil-prices", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "982512ebbfaf0f1a70393d8b9d39bee068fbd1179ba1c9060695fa666472cf69"}}, "hash": "93b8a3ada25c90b90c824d15a1db61d8042f829735f4de058995e406526fa29c", "text": "use of household appliances that help save women\u2019s time in domestic food processing and other household chores \u2013 though with the availability of electric light, women\u2019s workload can increase in the evenings. 90 Overcoming Vulnerability to Rising Oil Prices: Options for Asia and the Pacific Stage 1 \u2013 Present Stage 2 \u2013 Medium-term Stage 3 \u2013 Long-term Energy users Energy uses Rural households Traditional agriculture production Crop production Livestock Forestry Fisheries Post-harvest processing Heating Lighting Mechanical applications Rural households Traditional agriculture production Crop production Livestock Forestry Fisheries Post-harvest processing Heating Lighting Transport Other small mechanical power uses Other small electrical power uses Rural households Traditional agriculture production Crop production Livestock Forestry Fisheries Post-harvest processing Heating Lighting Transport Refrigeration Large heating applications Other small and large mechanical power uses Other small and large electrical power uses Energy resources Energy conversion and end-use technologies Human & animate power Fuelwood Crop wastes Animal dung Hydro Energy crops Wind Solar Human- and animal-driven devices Traditional stoves Traditional stoves \u2026.. \u2026.. \u2026.. Direct traditional solar drying Human- and animal-driven devices Gasifiers; charcoal and fuel briquettes; improved stoves Biogas systems; improved stoves Waterwheels; small decentralized hydro; and large grid-connected hydro \u2026\u2026 Windmills; decentralized wind power systems Improved solar driers; decentralized PV